results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Jade Horizon'
results.story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Jade Horizon’ delivers a pastel colorway of Tinker Hatfield’s 1990 design. A soft green hue is applied to the suede upper, equipped with clear quarter-panel netting and tonal TPU eyelets. Contrasting pink accents make their way to the Jumpman logo atop the silver reflective tongue, as well as the signature shark tooth detailing that decorates the black polyurethane midsole. Encapsulated Nike Air in the forefoot is joined by a visible Air sole unit in the heel, both of which are supported underfoot by an icy translucent outsole.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Blue Bird'
results.story: The women’s Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Blue Bird’ treats the retro silhouette to a vibrant makeover. An energetic shade of blue is executed on a suede upper furnished with standard AJ5 details, including lace locks, molded TPU eyelets and clear netting across the quarter panel. A blue Jumpman is embroidered atop a silver reflective tongue, complementing silver shark tooth detailing on the polyurethane midsole. Underfoot, an icy blue rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for maximum grip.

results.name: Air Jordan 11 Retro Low IE 'Bred' 2021
results.story: The 2021 reissue of the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low IE ‘Bred’ brings back the Chicago-inspired low-top originally released in 1996. A monochrome black finish is executed on the upper, constructed from a combination of leather, nubuck and breathable mesh — the latter material expressly chosen by Tinker Hatfield to accommodate the shoe’s original summertime release. A crimson Jumpman is embroidered on the tongue, matching the sneaker’s collar lining. The tooling is unchanged from the mid-top edition, highlighted by a translucent rubber outsole and carbon fiber shank.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Shimmer'
results.story: The women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Shimmer’ offers a subdued take on the classic silhouette forever tied to ‘The Shot.’ A monochromatic tan finish suffuses the leather upper, featuring structural wings, molded eyelets and quarter panel netting for enhanced breathability. The neutral color scheme is enlivened by a metallic silver Jumpman atop the tongue. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a polyurethane midsole, fitted with visible Air sole cushioning in the heel and supported by a herringbone-tread outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS 'Seafoam'
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS ‘Seafoam’ updates the iconic silhouette with a two-tone palette geared for the warm weather months. The upper is constructed from clean white leather with contrasting nubuck overlays in a pale green finish. The same pastel hue is repeated on the signature Swoosh, Nike branded tongue tag and durable rubber outsole. Woven white laces are outlined in reddish bronze for an unexpected pop of contrasting color.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Seafoam'
results.story: The women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Seafoam’ delivers a subtle two-tone colorway of the 1985 sneaker that started it all. The all-leather upper features a crisp white base with contrasting overlays in a soft green finish. The pastel hue is repeated on the sneaker’s branding elements, which include the signature Swoosh and Nike Air tongue tag. Contrasting color arrives via Healing Orange trim on the flat woven laces. The high-top is anchored by a durable rubber cupsole with encapsulated Air sole cushioning in the heel.

results.name: Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Twist'
results.story: The Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Twist’ projects a subtle take on the classic Chicago Bulls color palette. A pristine white finish on the stitched tumbled leather upper is matched by the signature lizard-textured mudguard. Sharp crimson accents land on the sneaker’s molded eyelets and a small midfoot overlay stamped with a Jordan wordmark. Contrasting black Jumpman branding decorates the tongue and webbing heel tab. The mid-top rides on a lightweight Phylon midsole with encapsulated full-length Zoom Air.

results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Oreo’ brings back a simple two-tone colorway first released in 2013. The build is faithful to the original, featuring a black suede upper with tonal TPU eyelets, translucent quarter panel netting and a grey Jumpman embroidered on the tongue. Contrasting white hits appear on the collar lining, interior tongue and Jumpman heel branding. The mid-top sits on a white polyurethane midsole with a visible Air unit nestled in the heel and black shark-tooth detailing dusted in white speckles. Underfoot, an icy rubber outsole delivers stop-and-go traction.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS 'Electro Orange'
results.story: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS ‘Electro Orange’ features a familiar color palette that recalls the original ‘Shattered Backboard’ release from 2015. The high-top carries a white leather upper with contrasting black hits on the eyestay, forefoot overlay and nylon tongue, the latter embellished with a woven Nike Air tag. On the lateral ankle flap, the Jordan Wings logo is stamped in black, matching the signature Swoosh. Contrasting orange accents land on the padded collar and rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Racer Blue'
results.story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Racer Blue’ showcases OG-inspired color blocking that recalls the shoe’s ‘Fire Red’ colorway from 1988. The upper is crafted from white tumbled leather with vibrant royal blue detailing on the sneaker’s eyelets, collar and polyurethane midsole, featuring visible Air sole cushioning under the heel. Additional blue accents land on standard Jumpman branding hits at the tongue and heel. Dual elephant-print overlays are updated with a pronounced crackle pattern.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro GS 'Racer Blue'
results.story: Offered in big kid sizing, the Air Jordan 3 Retro GS ‘Racer Blue’ is dressed in classic color blocking reminiscent of the OG ‘Fire Red’ colorway from 1988. Tumbled white leather is utilized on the upper, accented with dark grey elephant-print overlays at the toe and heel. Royal blue accents make their way to the sneaker’s molded eyelets, perforated leather collar and polyurethane midsole, enhanced with visible Air sole cushioning under the heel. The vibrant hue is repeated on Jumpman branding hits at the tongue and back heel.

results.name: Air Jordan 13 Retro Low GS 'Very Berry'
Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 PF 'Shattered Backboard'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 PF ‘Shattered Backboard’ updates Russell Westbrook’s signature shoe with a distinctive palette that takes inspiration from the coveted Air Jordan 1 colorway from 2015. The upper, constructed from off-white textile with reinforced synthetic overlays in orange and black, sits atop a cushy foam midsole with double-stacked Air Zoom units in the forefoot for extra-responsive cushioning. Exclusive to Asia, this PF version utilizes an extra-durable rubber outsole designed for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 'Shattered Backboard'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 ‘Shattered Backboard’ dresses Russell Westbrook’s signature shoe in a familiar color scheme that recalls the coveted Air Jordan 1 colorway that originally debuted in 2015. The upper is constructed from off-white textile with synthetic overlays in orange and black. Angular lines are accompanied by exposed zigzag stitching, while pink and yellow webbing straps offer unexpected pops of color. Responsive cushioning arrives via two stacked Air Zoom units nestled in the forefoot of the foam midsole.

results.name: Jordan Zion 1 PF 'Marion'
results.story: One of the initial colorways of Zion Williamson’s debut signature shoe, the Jordan Zion 1 PF ‘Marion’ gets its name from the athlete’s hometown in South Carolina, where he first picked up a basketball in middle school. The white textile upper is fortified with a metallic silver heel overlay and secured with dual pink and burgundy straps integrated into the lacing system. Extra-responsive cushioning is achieved by stacking a forefoot Zoom Air unit under a full-length Air Strobel. This PF version utilizes an extra-durable rubber outsole designed for outdoor play.

results.name: Air Jordan 35 Low PF 'White Black'
results.story: The Air Jordan 35 Low PF ‘White Black’ delivers an essential two-tone colorway of the performance hoops shoe, built with an upper that combines black textile with crisp white leather overlays. Contrasting pops of red land on a ‘23’ stamped on the lateral forefoot and a woven Nike Air tag stitched onto the back heel. Radiating Flightwire cables on the side panels give way to a glossy black Eclipse Plate 2.0, featuring a hollowed-out core that reveals Zoom Air cushioning in the heel and forefoot. This PF version uses an extra-durable rubber outsole made for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Jordan Zion 1 'Marion'
results.story: The Jordan Zion 1 ‘Marion’ draws inspiration from Zion Williamson’s South Carolina roots — specifically, the young athlete’s hometown when he first played basketball in middle school. The white textile upper is fortified with a metallic silver heel overlay and accented with pink and burgundy accents. The latter hue is repeated on the padded collar and articulated tongue, as well as a large ‘Z’ formation on the lateral side panel. Pink webbing straps are integrated into the laces for forefoot lockdown, while a full-length Air Strobel is stitched directly to the upper for responsive cushioning. A stacked Zoom Air unit in the forefoot provides added energy return.

results.name: Jordan Zion 1 PF 'Noah'
results.story: The Jordan Zion 1 PF ‘Noah’ celebrates the strong bond shared by Zion Williamson and his little brother. Doodle-like graphics throughout the upper draw inspiration from a trip to Nike’s global headquarters, where Noah customized an all-white Air Jordan 1 Low with crayons. Performance benefits include dual internal straps, a full-length Air Strobel, and a bottom-loaded Zoom Air unit stacked under the forefoot. This PF release makes use of an extra-durable rubber outsole intended for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Jordan Delta 2 GS 'Thermo White'
results.story: Constructed for big kids, the Jordan Delta 2 GS ‘Thermo White’ highlights contrasting tones on a lifestyle silhouette that blends comfort, craftsmanship and a modern, deconstructed aesthetic. Powder blue suede and white textile make up the composition of the upper, reinforced with a rigid mudguard and a black nubuck toe wrap. On the lateral side, a bright red Jumpman tag is affixed to the decorative suede eyestay. Matching crimson hits land on the woven tongue tag and extended heel tab. The sneaker rides on a Cushlon foam midsole, reinforced underfoot by durable rubber in high-wear areas.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 PF 'KB3'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 ‘KB3 PF showcases an airy build on Russell Westbrook’s fourth signature shoe. The sneaker makes use of a slate blue mesh upper, accented with lavender webbing straps integrated into the lacing system for a lockdown fit. Responsive cushioning arrives via double-stacked Air Zoom units nestled in the forefoot of the full-length foam midsole. This PF version is exclusive to the Asian market and features an extra-durable rubber outsole made for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro TD 'Flint' 2021
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 7 Retro TD ‘Flint’ brings back the 2006 colorway in toddler sizing. A webbing pull tab at the heel allows for easy entry into an upper crafted from grey nubuck and white synthetic leather. ‘Jordan’ is inscribed in violet lettering on the plush tongue, matching an embroidered Jumpman on the collar and ‘23’ branding on the heel. The sneaker sits atop a soft foam midsole, supported underfoot by a durable rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro GS 'Flint' 2021
results.story: The 2021 reissue of the Air Jordan 7 Retro GS ‘Flint’ brings back a 2006 colorway in big kid sizing. The mid-top makes use of a grey nubuck upper with white tumbled leather overlays and a Huarache-like inner sleeve for a snug, comfortable fit. Court Purple accents make their way to Air Jordan lettering on the tongue, an embroidered Jumpman on the lateral collar and a raised ‘23’ on the angular heel patch. The sneaker rides on a foam midsole with Nike Air cushioning in the heel for improved impact protection.

results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro PS 'Flint' 2021
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 7 Retro PS ‘Flint’ revives a 2006 colorway for little kids. The outward design is true to the original, featuring an upper that combines grey nubuck with tumbled white leather. ‘Air Jordan’ is embroidered in purple lettering on the signature Air Jordan 7 tongue, connected to a Huarache-like inner sleeve and covered in a unique geometric print. Matching violet accents appear on a Jumpman logo on the lateral collar and a molded ‘23’ on the heel patch.

results.name: Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro PS 'British Khaki'
results.story: Built for little kids, the Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro PS ‘British Khaki’ delivers a refined take on the classic mid-top. Soft suede in a dark tan finish makes up the composition of the upper, equipped with a button stash pocket on the lateral collar and a zippered pouch on the medial side. A Jumpman icon in Bright Crimson stands out on the canvas tongue, matched by Nike Air and Cactus Jack logos on the heel of the left and right shoe. They’re joined by the Houston rapper’s personal branding hits on the medial-side midsole and semi-translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro TD 'British Khaki'
results.story: The Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro TD ‘British Khaki’ scales the down the collaborative release for a new generation of sneaker enthusiasts. The mid-top is outfitted in a tan suede upper with stash pouches on both sides of the collar. Bright Crimson accents make their way to Jumpman branding on the canvas tongue, along with mismatched Nike and Cactus Jack logos on each heel. The sneaker rides on a soft foam midsole, reinforced underfoot by a glow-in-the-dark rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan Zion 1 PS 'Gen Zion'
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Jordan Zion 1 PS ‘Gen Zion’ represents the debut colorway of Zion Williamson’s first signature shoe. Black mesh is utilized on the upper, bolstered with a white synthetic overlay that wraps around the heel and extends to the midfoot, culminating in a ‘Z’ formation on the lateral side. Additional nods to the athlete take the form of an all-over ‘Zion’ print on the collar and a ZW logo stamped on the left tongue, complementing a matching gold Jumpman on the right. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a plush foam midsole, reinforced by a decoupled icy rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan Zion 1 TD 'Gen Zion'
results.story: The Jordan Zion 1 TD ‘Gen Zion’ delivers a miniaturized version of Zion Williamson’s debut signature shoe in its launch colorway. No-tie laces are integrated into a hook-and-loop eyelet that completely detaches, allowing the shoe to be easily slipped on and off. The two-tone upper, constructed from black mesh with white synthetic leather, sits atop a cushy foam sole unit that offers soft landings for little feet. Metallic gold branding elements include a Jumpman icon on the right tongue and a ZW logo on the left.

results.name: Jordan Zion 1 GS 'Gen Zion'
results.story: The Jordan Zion 1 GS ‘Gen Zion’ presents the launch colorway of Zion Williamson’s debut signature shoe in big kid sizing. Celebrating the athlete’s status as a generational talent, the mid-top carries a black mesh upper with a contrasting white synthetic overlay and a graffiti-like ‘Zion’ print throughout the padded textile collar. Gleaming pops of metallic gold land on branding elements that include a Jumpman icon on the right tongue, a ZW logo on the left, and ‘Zion’ inscribed on the heel tab. The sneaker rides on a full-length foam midsole, supported underfoot by an icy translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 High FlyEase GS 'Light Smoke Grey'
Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 'Marathon'
results.story: Drawing inspiration from the Indianapolis 500 and the event’s iconic racing suit designs, the Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 ‘Marathon’ features an energetic blend of colors throughout the breathable textile upper. Russell Westbrook’s personal logo is embroidered on the tongue, while a checkerboard overlay adds an additional motorsport flourish. The lightweight build is supported by a lightweight Phylon midsole with a TPU shank and double-stacked Zoom Air units in the forefoot.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid TD 'Black Gym Red'
Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Black Gym Red'
Air Jordan 1 Low GS 'Light Arctic Pink'
Air Jordan 5 Retro PS 'Stealth 2.0'
results.story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro PS ‘Stealth 2.0’ brings back a 2006 colorway in little kid sizing. The mid-top silhouette features a tumbled white leather upper with semi-translucent netting on the quarter panels and light grey molded eyelets. A royal blue Jumpman adorns a silver reflective tongue, matching the sneaker’s lace locks and collar lining. A second Jumpman icon is embroidered on the back heel. This scaled-down edition features a full-length foam midsole that lacks the visible Air heel unit of the original.

results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro TD 'Stealth 2.0'
results.story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro TD ‘Stealth 2.0’ celebrates the 15th anniversary of a popular colorway in scaled-down build made for growing feet. Like the original, the upper is constructed from tumbled white leather with Jumpman branding on the heel. A second Jumpman decorates a silver reflective tongue, a hallmark feature of Tinker Hatfield’s 1990 design. It’s joined by additional AJ5 floursihes, including quarter panel netting and shark tooth detailing on the midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 12 Retro PS 'Arctic Pink'
results.story: Built for little kids, the Air Jordan 12 Retro PS ‘Arctic Pink’ delivers a refreshed take on the classic silhouette that Michael Jordan wore when he captured his fifth NBA title. In addition to the non-traditional palette, the stitched upper is treated to a distressed finish, featuring textured pink remnants that create an abstract pattern on a light grey backdrop. A more intense shade of pink lands on the sneaker’s collar lining, pull tab and branding elements, which include an embroidered Jumpman atop the tongue.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro PS 'Georgetown'
results.story: Crafted for little kids, the Air Jordan 3 Retro PS ‘Georgetown’ features the signature colors of the Hoyas, the first in a long line of competitors felled by Michael Jordan with the final shot in a title game. The upper is built with navy tumbled leather, accented with grey elephant-print overlays at the toe and heel. Both the sneaker’s tongue and molded heel tab are trimmed with iconic Jumpman branding. A foam midsole delivers a cushioned ride, absent the visible Air sole unit of the mainline release.

results.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro TD 'Georgetown'
results.story: The Air Jordan 3 Retro TD ‘Georgetown’ gives the vintage model a scaled-down makeover that leaves the sneaker’s iconic details intact. They include an embroidered Jumpman icon on the grey leather leather tongue and elephant-print overlays at the toe and heel. Combined with a navy tumbled leather upper, the resulting palette is redolent of the signature hues of the Georgetown Hoyas, the team that Michael Jordan and the Tar Heels defeated in the ‘82 NCAA championship game.

results.name: Jayson Tatum x Air Jordan 35 'Greatest Gift'
results.story: Crafted specifically for the NBA star, the Jayson Tatum x Air Jordan 35 ‘Greatest Gift’ showcases a vibrant mix of colors that pay tribute to the athlete’s mother and grandmother. On the left shoe, the red patent leather tongue is embroidered with Tatum’s initials, while a purple midfoot overlay displays his birth year. The latter hue is repeated on toe box detailing inscribed with the phrase ‘Women in Power.’ Custom sockliners give the nod to Jordan Brand’s ‘Fearless Ones’ campaign, spotlighting individuals who strive for positive change within their communities.

results.name: Jayson Tatum x Air Jordan 35 PF 'Greatest Gift'
results.story: A PE colorway made for the NBA star, the Jayson Tatum x Air Jordan 35 PF ‘Greatest Gift’ features a vibrant design that honors the most important women in the athlete’s life. The sneaker’s mesh and patent leather upper is finished in a bold palette that reflects the favorite colors of his mother. ‘Women in Power’ is inscribed on the toe box, while a hand-drawn ‘98’ on the lateral side denotes Tatum’s birth year. This PF version is exclusive to Asia and features an extra-durable rubber outsole built for play on outdoor courts.

results.name: Jordan MA2 'Vast Grey'
results.story: The Jordan MA2 ‘Vast Grey’ delivers a neutral colorway of the lifestyle silhouette that takes its cues from the Jordan Max 200. The grey textile upper is fortified with tonal suede overlays and equipped with an extended heel and exposed-foam tongue, both of which are appended with webbing pull tabs for easy on and off. Contrasting yellow accents land on the sneaker’s textured rubber heel clip and large-volume Max Air unit, offering lightweight cushioning with each step.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Purple Pulse Glacier Blue'
Air Jordan 1 Mid SE TD 'All Star 2021'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE TD ‘All Star 2021’ delivers a two-tone colorway of the classic silhouette made for growing basketball fans. The sneaker features a leather upper that combines a crisp white base with glossy black overlays in a faux carbon fiber print. Along with an added pull tab at the heel, the mid-top is appointed standard Air Jordan 1 details, including a perforated toe box and a solid rubber outsole originally designed for pivoting on the hardwood.

results.name: Jordan Delta Mid 'Hasta'
results.story: The Jordan Delta Mid ‘Hasta’ showcases an eclectic build, featuring a mix of slate blue mesh, grey textile and nubuck, and black synthetic leather. The materials coalesce on an upper nearly devoid of traditional Jordan branding, save for a small Jumpman and an abstract Wings logo on the woven tongue tag. The tech-inspired lifestyle sneaker is mounted on a full-length Nike React midsole, treated to a cream-colored finish and molded with grooved sidewalls for reduced weight and enhanced flexibility.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro Little Flex TD 'Carmine'
Air Jordan 6 Retro TD 'Carmine' 2021
results.story: This 2021 reissue of the Air Jordan 6 Retro TD ‘Carmine’ brings back an OG colorway of the classic silhouette, drastically scaled down for a new generation of Michael Jordan fans. The color-blocked upper combines a red leather base with contrasting white leather overlays, both featuring perforated detailing for improved breathability. Embroidered Nike branding on the heel delivers an OG touch. Underfoot, a red Jumpman logo adorns the white rubber outsole, featuring forefoot flex grooves for a comfortable stride.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid SE PS 'Take Flight'
Air Jordan 1 Mid SE TD 'Take Flight'
Air Jordan 1 Mid SE GS 'Take Flight'
Air Jordan 9 Retro GS 'Dark Charcoal University Gold'
results.story: Crafted for big kids, the Air Jordan 9 Retro GS ‘Dark Charcoal University Gold’ presents a subdued colorway of the silhouette that released when Michael Jordan had temporarily stepped away from the game. Black and charcoal tones are applied to the nubuck upper, equipped with interior bootie construction and a speed lacing system. Contrasting hits of University Gold land on the collar lining and heel, featuring a webbing pull tab and an embroidered 23. A matching gold Jumpman adorns the PU midsole, housing an encapsulated Air unit in the heel.

results.name: Air Jordan 9 Retro TD 'Dark Charcoal University Gold'
results.story: The Air Jordan 9 Retro TD ‘Dark Charcoal University Gold’ delivers a scaled-down version of the classic silhouette that originally released in 1993. The mid-top sports a synthetic nubuck upper in subdued black and charcoal grey tones, contrasted by University Gold accents on the collar lining and webbing pull tab. The vibrant yellow hue makes repeat appearances on the sneaker’s branding elements, including an embroidered 23 on the heel and a Jumpman icon on the lateral midsole.

results.name: FACETASM x Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 Premium 'Smokey Blue'
results.story: Launching as part of a collaborative capsule with Hiromichi Ochiai’s progressive fashion brand, the FACETASM x Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 updates Russell Westbrook’s fourth signature shoe with a layered build constructed from textile, suede and synthetic leather. Aggressive color blocking and sharp, angular lines are accompanied by unique textures, include a furry tongue and quilted collar lining. FACETASM branding lands on an orange woven tab atop the toe box and a matching orange heel loop on the right shoe.

results.name: FACETASM x Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 Premium PF 'Smokey Blue'
Air Jordan 1 Mid SE PS 'Red Quilted'
Jordan Delta Mid 'Storm Blue'
results.story: The Jordan Delta Mid ‘Storm Blue’ applies black, grey and navy tones to a lifestyle silhouette feauturing multilayered construction for a unique handcrafted look. An integrated lacing system secures an upper built with a combination of mesh, textile, nubuck and synthetic suede. Webbing pull tabs are attached to the heel and exposed foam tongue for easy on and off, while the seamless interior provides abrasion-free comfort. The mid-top is mounted on a full-length Nike React midsole, supported by a gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 GS 'Family'
results.story: Crafted for big kids, the Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 GS ‘Family’ celebrates the people and communities that Russell Westbrook holds dear. Metallic gold accents stand out on a breathable black mesh upper, featuring a lockdown fit via interior straps looped into the lacing system. The lightweight build rides on a contrasting white foam midsole, reinforced with a rubber outsole split into two discrete sections that enhance flexibility while reducing the shoe’s overall weight.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 'Family'
results.story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 ‘Family’ dresses Russell Westbrook’s fourth signature shoe in a simplistic color scheme that celebrates the most important people and communities in the athlete’s personal orbit. The performance hoops shoe makes use of a breathable black mesh upper, accented with a metallic gold heel tab and matching branding elements. Under the ball of the foot, double stacked Air Zoom units enhance the foam midsole, reinforced by a split rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 35 'Bred'
results.story: The Air Jordan 35 ‘Bred’ takes on an iconic color scheme that’s virtually synonymous with the Jordan franchise at large. A mostly black finish is executed on the upper, featuring a blend of suede, mesh and grid-like netting that recalls the Air Jordan 5. Flecks of red can be seen on the Flightwire cables that radiate out from the sneaker’s side panels. Additional pops of Fire Red land on the Jumpman logo on the silver reflective tongue — another carryover from the AJ5 — and Eclipse Plate, supported by a matching herringbone outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 35 GS 'Bred'
results.story: Made for grade schoolers, the Air Jordan 35 GS ‘Bred’ dresses the performance hoops shoe in a color scheme baked into the DNA of the Jordan franchise. The black finish of the suede and mesh upper is contrasted by a silver reflective tongue that recalls the Air Jordan 5, complete with a Jumpman icon in Fire Red. Additional flecks of crimson land on the Flightwire cables that reinforce the sneaker’s side panels. A color-fade effect in black and red is applied to the Eclipse Plate, with the latter hue seeping into the herringbone rubber outsole.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 TD 'Upbringing'
results.story: Made for toddlers, the Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 TD ‘Upbringing’ features a vibrant design inspired by Russell Westbrook’s early days growing up in Southern California. Mismatched color blocking is applied to an upper that combines breathable mesh with synthetic nubuck and leather overlays. Westbrook’s personal logo adorns an adjustable hook-and-loop strap that wraps over the midfoot for an extra-secure fit. The bright assemblage of colors up top is offset by a white foam sole unit, equipped with flex grooves that allow little feet to move freely and comfortably.

results.name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 GS 'Upbringing'
results.story: Built for big kids, the Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 GS ‘Upbringing' features mismatched prints and colors on the upper of the left and right shoe, resulting in a kaleidoscopic design that takes inspiration from Russell Westbrook’s formative years in Southern California. The complex build combines breathable mesh with lightweight textile, synthetic overlays and cracked leather paneling on the heel. Zoom Air cushioning is housed in the heel of the foam midsole, supported by a decoupled translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Wmns Air Jordan 1 Low 'Triple Black Quilted'
